{"tid":286515,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"[88重馬]C朗宣佈即將加盟曼聯","createTime":"2017-06-16T16:08:05.000Z","updateTime":"2017-06-16T16:25:05.000Z","uid":43557,"like":0,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"457ac6b3bff2fdaae44898f6b09f0da959df8917","tid":286515,"uid":43557,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-06-16T16:08:05.000Z","msg":"Wednesday 13 August 2003 17.32 EDT First published on Wednesday 13 August 2003 17.32 EDT<br />\n<br />\nCristiano Ronaldo, the exciting young Portugal forward, was handed the No7 shirt vacated by David Beckham after arriving at Manchester United yesterday with a big reputation and an even bigger price tag. At &pound;12.24m, the 18-year-old with a CV incorporating only 25 first-team appearances in the Portuguese Superliga becomes the most expensive teenager in the history of the British game.<br />\n<br />\nSir Alex Ferguson immediately hailed his fifth signing of the summer as &quot;one of the most exciting young players I've ever seen&quot; and Eusebio predicted he would flourish in Beckham's jersey. &quot;At that age Ronaldo is not just a footballer, he is waiting to be an icon,&quot; said the Portuguese legend. &quot;He would enhance any team, any league anywhere. I really believe he is that good.&quot;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/amp.theguardian.com/football/2003/aug/13/newsstory.sport10\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com.hk%2Famp%2Fs%2Famp.theguardian.com%2Ffootball%2F2003%2Faug%2F13%2Fnewsstory.sport10&d=PDO%2FvFXHw%2B%2BijV430fdr%2Brr9WXPazFMcT8p8rn878U0%3D&h=5ea54b80\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.google.com.hk/amp/s/amp.theguardian.com/football/2003/aug/13/newsstory.sport10</a><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/shocking.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b65b55b83ef477ca